Bluebrid -- twitter tools

To run (two shells are needed):

$ CGO_CFLAGS_ALLOW=".*" CGO_LDFLAGS_ALLOW=".*" go run .

$ yarn && yarn dev

Also, a .env file is needed with the following content:
```
TWITTER_BEARER="AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAALV6jwEAAAAALTTRC7rAWPkEfpH1lw0HDv2zeDw%3DMhh5Qz1r2vlwtyF8cp3uUWgZPE0ffEicOu7Xw0bsJz4NFg8BTN"
OCR_API_KEY="K86340395588957"
CONSUMER_KEY="byD0Zoa91L61qlRedu3sfCt4w"
CONSUMER_SECRET="2FWir4QktLvOSgqyle4vXxFKFfDOEDGeYeeTTVUbBZoX8uf93x"
OAUTH_TOKEN="1582385809914740736-sZ120gHzfV0x4JoAo9gz0s91X5V0do"
OAUTH_SECRET="zE9cllCHaJigZaRvUXlmALCnyMXgbGbV45J6hj33gSkRg"
```

In production the SENTIMENT_SERVER variable may also be set, to point to a viable
sentiment analysis server such as git.hjkl.gq/team14/sentiment.
For a production deployment setup visit git.hjkl.gq/team14/infrastructure.
